-- Alstom board accepts 10 bln euro GE offer for energy unit-paper
-- By Geert De Clercq and Lewis Krauskopf
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 04:23PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, April 29 (Reuters) - The board of French trains-to-turbines maker Alstom has accepted General Electric's <GE.N> 10 billion euro offer for its energy division, French daily Le Figaro said on its website.

Alstom declined to comment on the report. The firm will issue a statement Wednesday morning around 7 a.m. (0500 GMT). GE also declined to comment.